WRITING RULES (apply identically to every locale):
- FORMAT: Continuous prose in paragraphs only. Lists or bullet points are STRICTLY PROHIBITED.
- LENGTH: The description field MUST contain between 250 and 400 words. No exceptions.
- DATA INTEGRITY: Use only facts explicitly present in the property data above.
  Never infer, approximate, or invent details that are not provided. If a detail is absent, omit it.
- NARRATIVE STRUCTURE (four paragraphs):
    1. Introduction (~60–80 words): Emotional hook with location and property type. Must include the primary keyword.
    2. Interior (~80–100 words): Comfort, design, bedroom layout, standout spaces.
    3. Technical Features (~60–80 words): Translate specs into tangible lifestyle benefits — never list, always narrate.
    4. Outdoor & CTA (~60–80 words): Plot, garage, outdoor potential. Close with a generic, culturally appropriate CTA. Must include at least one secondary keyword.
- TITLE FORMAT: [Typology] [Key Feature] in [Location] — [Differentiator]. Max 60 characters. Must include the primary keyword or its natural equivalent.
- TONE OF VOICE: Professional, inspiring, and modern.
- KEYWORDS: The provided keywords may be in a different language than the target locale.
  Adapt their meaning naturally — do NOT insert foreign-language keywords verbatim into the text.
- CONTENT FILTER: Exclude all agency-specific references (names, contacts, taglines).

